<paragraph blockId="127.[189,1399,1209,1271]" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">
The specific epithet is from the Latin ‘ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin" authorityYear="2018" box="[654,800,1210,1235]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="127" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrotarsata">
<emphasis box="[654,800,1210,1235]" italics="true" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">nigrotarsata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’, meaning ‘with black tarsus’ and referring to the predominantly black protarsus.
</paragraph>
