<paragraph blockId="129.[189,1399,401,674]" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">
ABDOMEN. Length ratio of terga I: II: III: IV 1: 3.2–3.6: 2.3–2.6: 1.8–2.1; ratio width at posterior margin: medial length of tergum II and III 1: 4.6–5.0 and 1: 1.0–1.3. Terga black, anterior ¼ of tergum III with straight yellow fascia; anterior 1/5 of tergum IV with yellow posteromedially incised fascia; pile pale, on terga short, laterally on terga I and II long; tergum I with horizontal row of 2 strong dark brown to light yellow setae at lateral margin; sternum III rectangular, ratio width: length 1: 2.2–3.4; sternum IV, 
<figureCitation box="[189,297,577,603]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="129.[189,232,1931,1957]" captionTargetBox="[198,1390,809,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@129.[189,1399,796,1903]" captionTargetPageId="129" captionText="Fig. 62. Sphegina (Asiosphegina) nigrotarsata sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ. A. Sternum IV, ventral view. B. Left surstylus, lateral view. C. Left superior lobe with associated parts, lateral view. D. Genitalia, right side, lateral view. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3830680" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3830680/files/figure.png" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Fig. 62A</figureCitation>
; sterna VI, VII and VIII simple, with long yellow pile. Genitalia, 
<figureCitation box="[1073,1158,577,603]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="129.[189,232,1931,1957]" captionTargetBox="[198,1390,809,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@129.[189,1399,796,1903]" captionTargetPageId="129" captionText="Fig. 62. Sphegina (Asiosphegina) nigrotarsata sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ. A. Sternum IV, ventral view. B. Left surstylus, lateral view. C. Left superior lobe with associated parts, lateral view. D. Genitalia, right side, lateral view. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3830680" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3830680/files/figure.png" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Fig. 62</figureCitation>
B–D: note the group of long seta-like pile on cercus, nearly symmetrical surstyli and superior lobes and the small setae on the membrane at the surstylar apodemes.
</paragraph>
